				</p>
				<h3>To Un-Install the Plugin:</h3>
				<p>This add-on lives entirely in the override and template system, so there is no need to remove it. Simply switch back to your custom template using the admin panel.</p>
<p>
But if you wish to uninstall completely, remove all simple_responsive files and restore your backup files.</p>
				

	</div>
<p>
Restore your backup for <span class="tomato-txt">includes/templates/YOUR_TEMPLATE/common/tpl_main_page.php</span>.</p>
<p>
Restore your <span class="tomato-txt">includes/templaes/YOUR_TEMPLATE/css/index_home.css</span> file.
</p>

