				<div id="admin">
				<h2>Admin Settings</h2>
				<p>Some things still may look a bit odd. Most of those can be adjusted using your Administrations Panel.<br>Log in to your admin panel. Find these settings and change them:</p>
				<p><i class="fa fa-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>  Under Configuration > <span class="fuscia">Images</span></p>
				<code>Subcategory Image Width	= 80%	</code><br>
<code>Subcategory Image Height =  80%</code>
<p>This seems to work best set between 75% and 85%, but both numbers should be the same. the width used in the 'tryit' section is<br> (Adding the percentage sign (%) changes the width and height so it uses percentages instead of pixels.)</p><hr>
	<p><i class="fa fa-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>  Under Configuration >  <span class="fuscia">Product Listing</span></p>
				<code>Display Product Price/Add to Cart =	0 (off)	</code><br>
				<p>Or, leave it on and set:</p>
<code>Display Product Price/Add to Cart Column Width	= 10%</code><br><p>This allows a bit more space for the item attributes.</p>

<p><i class="fa fa-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>  Under Configuration >  <span class="fuscia">Layout</span></p>
				<code>Column Width - Left Boxes = 100%</code><br>
				<code>Column Width - Right Boxes = 100%</code><br>
				<code>Column Width - Left = 100%</code><br>
				<code>Column Width - Right = 100%	</code><br>
				
			
